## Thundering Herd Problem

When a popular cache entry expires, thousands of requests simultaneously hit the DB:

```
10:00:00 — cache entry expires
10:00:01 — 5000 requests arrive, all miss, all query DB
           DB overwhelmed → cascading failure!
```

### Solutions:
1. **Mutex/Lock** — first request acquires lock, others wait
2. **Probabilistic early expiration** — randomly refresh before TTL expires
3. **Background refresh** — async worker refreshes before expiry
4. **Stale-while-revalidate** — serve stale data while refreshing async

```java
// Redis mutex pattern
String lockKey = "lock:" + cacheKey;
boolean acquired = redis.set(lockKey, "1", SetArgs.Builder.nx().ex(5));
if (acquired) {
    // load from DB, update cache
    redis.del(lockKey);
} else {
    // Wait briefly and retry from cache
    Thread.sleep(50);
    return redis.get(cacheKey);
}
```
